Nelson Mandela Bay ANC councillor Mike Kwenaite has died, the party confirmed on Tuesday. Kwenaite, who  was sworn in as a councillor in January after  former deputy mayor Bicks Ndoni died,  succumbed  to Covid-19 complications. His  death was confirmed by ANC regional task team co-ordinator Luyolo Nqakula on Tuesday. Kwenaite, from Uitenhage, has a long history in the Bay council, having served on the mayoral committee member for a number of years. This is a developing story HeraldLIVE